programme.title: Live Betfred Super League
programme.desc: Leeds Rhinos v Hull FC (Kick-off 7.45pm). Coverage of the match from the fifth round of fixtures, which takes place at Emerald Headingley Stadium. This match is a repeat of the semi-final encounter from last September, which the home side won 18-16. The Rhinos dominated the early stages, with Stevie Ward and Anthony Mullally giving them a 12-0 lead. However, tries from Gareth Ellis, Mahe Fonua and Sika Manu saw the Airlie Birds edge in front, but Liam Sutcliffe powered his way over to set up a showdown with Castleford Tigers at Old Trafford, which the Rhinos would also win 24-6

programme.title: Live Premier League Darts
programme.desc: Coverage of the sixth round of the season, which comes from the First Direct Arena in Leeds, where Michael van Gerwen continues the defence of his title. This week's fixtures see van Gerwen take on Australia's Simon Whitlock, while Gerwyn Price faces Raymond van Barneveld and Peter Wright meets Mensur Suljovic. Plus, Gary Anderson v Daryl Gurney and Rob Cross v Michael Smith
